    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">1, Savile Row, | Burlington Gardens, | W.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Nov 15 1873</date>
                    <salute>My dear Mr Darwin</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Enclosed is Wallace’s reply.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> You will perceive that he is at present unaware of the scope &amp; nature of the revision required, &amp; I should think they ought to be <hi rend="underline">very</hi> <hi rend="underline">exactly</hi> defined if he is employed; otherwise he would be likely to query the reasoning.</p>
<p>Yours sincerely | H W Bates</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
        <div type="enclosure" subtype="letter">
      
          <opener>
                    <placeName>The Dell, Grays, Essex.</placeName>
                    <date>Nov<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. 14th. 1873</date>
                    <salute>Dear Bates</salute>
                </opener><div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Thanks for your note. I shall be glad to undertake the revision of Darwin’s Descent of Man—always supposing Mr Darwin likes me to do it, &amp; also that it is <hi rend="underline">well paid for</hi>, as it will be a stiff job.</p>
<p>I shall be very glad to see &amp; review Belt’s Book.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>In haste | Yours very faithfully | Alfred R. Wallace</p> 
                </div>
        
    </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD had evidently asked Bates to write to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4935.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Alfred Russel Wallace</ref> to enquire whether he was willing to revise <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> for a second edition.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Wallace’s review of <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_383.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Thomas Belt’s</ref> <hi rend="italic">The naturalist in Nicaragua</hi> (Belt 1874) appeared in <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi>, 22 January 1874, pp. 218–21.</note>
        </div>        
            
